ience that would come to define epic theater, and that his revisions to the theory of Gestus in the mid-1930s are reminiscent of nineteenth-century opera performance practices of mimesis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aOpera. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Opera.2bisacsh  a19th century opera performance.  abertolt brecht.  abrecht criticism.  abrecht.  adialectical theater.  aepic theater.  agerman drama.  agerman literature.  agerman plays.  agerman playwright.  ahanns eisler.  akurt weill.  alehrstuck.  amusicology.  aopera in brecht.  aopera.  apaul dessau.  apaul hindemith.  aperforming arts.  atheory of gestus.  aweimar playwright.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052031426940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520942813?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520942813423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520942813/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY